        "part_1": {
            "name": "First steps",
            "chapter_1": {
                "name": "Welcome üëã",
                "summary": "Some tipps to get you started",
                "content": "<p>You are here, which means - you decided to write your very own novel! Congratulations for that! üéâ</p><p>The following chapters will give you a small tour of what you can do.</p><h2>üëâ Let's go!</h2><blockquote><p>In the chapter list, select the next chapter to proceed!</p><img class=\"my-custom-class\" src=\"/assets/images/getting-started/en/getting-started-select-next-chapter.gif\"></blockquote><blockquote><p>üí° By the way: You can select multiple items by using the Shift or Ctrl Key while clicking on an item.</p></blockquote><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p>"
            },
            "chapter_2": {
                "name": "How chapters are organized ‚ûï",
                "summary": "Adding parts and chapters",
                "content": "<p>You may already have noticed the tab menu on top of the application and seen that wortomat gives you space for organizing your <em>chapters, characters, research </em>and <em>locations</em>.</p><p>All of these items are organized into groups, e.g. a <em>part</em> consists of multiple <em>chapters</em>.</p><h2>üëâ<strong> Create a new group</strong></h2><blockquote><p>To create new group, click on the big plus button in the side menu.</p><img class=\"my-custom-class\" src=\"/assets/images/getting-started/en/getting-started-add-group.gif\"></blockquote><h2>üëâ<strong> Rename the group</strong></h2><blockquote><p>You see the placeholder text where the name of the new group should be? Click on it, and give your new group some nice title.</p><img class=\"my-custom-class\" src=\"/assets/images/getting-started/en/getting-started-rename-group.gif\"></blockquote><blockquote><p>You can also use enter and escape keys for confirming or canceling your changes.</p></blockquote><h2>üëâ<strong> Create a new item within the new group</strong></h2><blockquote><p>To add a new chapter click on the plus button next to the newly created group. The new chapter will automatically be selected, so make sure to come back here afterwards üòâ</p><img class=\"my-custom-class\" src=\"/assets/images/getting-started/en/getting-started-add-child.gif\"></blockquote><p></p>"
            },
            "chapter_3": {
                "name": "Renaming and editing üñäÔ∏è",
                "summary": "",
                "content": "<p>You maybe already noticed that each chapter has</p><ul><li><p>A title</p></li><li><p>A summary</p></li><li><p>Tags</p></li><li><p>The content</p></li></ul><p>The chapter you are <strong>currently</strong> reading does not have a summary or any tags yet - you just see some placeholder text instead.</p><h2>üëâ Edit the summary</h2><blockquote><p>Click on the placeholder text for the summary and give it some nice summary.</p><img class=\"my-custom-class\" src=\"/assets/images/getting-started/en/getting-started-edit-summary.gif\"></blockquote><h2>üëâ Add a tag</h2><blockquote><p>Click on the placeholder text for the tags and add the tag <em>Tutorial</em>You can also create a new tag just by typing it into the field</p><img class=\"my-custom-class\" src=\"/assets/images/getting-started/en/getting-started-edit-tags.gif\"></blockquote><h2>üëâ Explore the content editor</h2><blockquote><p>Click on the content (the thing you are currently reading) and have a look around at what you can do in the text editor</p></blockquote><blockquote><p></p></blockquote><h2></h2>"
            }
